metadata.name: Goddess
metadata.description:
...a Pagan Goddess born again like a phoenix from the flames...transforming into an Owl...

"So they took the blossoms of the oak, and the blossoms of the broom, and the blossoms of the meadow-sweet, and produced from them a maiden, the fairest and most graceful that man ever saw. And they baptized her, and gave her the name of Blodeuwedd..."
She follows her own heart & for punishment is transformed into a huge Owl ; Blodeuwedd in Welsh means 'flower-face' [the Mabinogion]

Ink, Pencil & Watercolour [Bg textures in Psp]
